iss%20peak%20covered%20with%20snow%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651d55c92ce014759e7456dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Laser%20Lightning%20Rod%20was%20placed%20near%20a%20telecommunications%20tower%20on%20top%20of%20a%20Swiss%20peak%2C%20known%20to%20be%20hit%20more%20than%20100%20times%20per%20year%20by%20lightning.%20%3Cp%3ESource%3A%20TRUMPF%20group%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20this%20channel%20is%20very%20short-lived%2C%20and%20laser%20beams%20flicker.%20Though%20scientists%20had%20been%20able%20to%20deflect%20lightning%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpolytechnique.hal.science%2Fhal-00852030%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20lab%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they'd%20never%20been%20able%20to%20do%20it%20in%20real-life%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20sure%20the%20channel%20stayed%20open%20long%20enough%20to%20bend%20lightning%20during%20a%20storm%2C%20scientists%20developed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbreakthrough-starshot-laser-beam-power-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaser%3C%2Fa%3E%20able%20to%20fire%20high-powered%20pulses%201%2C000%20times%20per%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20a%20joint%20effort%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Geneva%20(UNIGE)%20and%20EPFL%20in%20Switzerland%2C%20the%20%C3%89cole%20Polytechnique%20in%20France%2C%20and%20TRUMPF%20scientific%20lasers%20firm%20in%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20laser%20pulsed%20100%20times%20faster%20than%20their%20previous%20laser%2C%20which%20means%20the%20laser%20is%20%26quot%3B100%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20catch%20lightning%2C%26quot%3B%20Houard%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Flasers-can-guide-dangerous-lightning-strikes-to-a-safer-path-study-shows-11673884829%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETesting%20the%20laser%20at%20the%20top%20of%20a%20Swiss%20mountain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20test%20the%20new%20gear%2C%20the%20scientists%20brought%20their%203-ton%20laser%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%208%2C000-foot-high%20Mount%20S%C3%A4ntis%20in%20Switzerland.%20The%20advantage%20of%20this%20location%20is%20its%20400-foot%20communications%20tower%2C%20which%20is%20reliably%20hit%20by%20lightning%20at%20least%20100%20times%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20laser%20was%20powered%20up%20any%20time%20the%20weather%20forecast%20predicted%20thunderstorms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20the%20scientists%20were%20able%20to%20record%20a%20natural%20lightning%20bolt%20that%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20followed%20the%20laser%20beam%20before%20hitting%20the%20tower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20analyze%20a%20lot%20more%20data%20following%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jean-Pierre%20Wolf%2C%20professor%20of%20applied%20physics%20at%20UNIGE%2C%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unige.ch%2Fmedias%2Fen%2F2023%2Fdevier-la-foudre-grace-au-paratonnerre-laser%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20video%20accompanying%20the%20findings%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20French.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20that%20picture%20spoke%20a%20thousand%20words%2C%20there%20was%20no%20doubt%20possible.%20When%20I%20saw%20this%20picture%2C%20I%20knew%20we%20had%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20images%20show%20lightning%20seemingly%20curving%20away%20from%20its%20path%20to%20follow%20a%20bright%20laser%20beam%20being%20shot%20toward%20the%20sky%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651d5a60617692f0d03ea14d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22351%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwo%20side%20by%20side%20pictures%20show%20a%20lightning%20bolt%20super%20imposed%20over%20a%20picture%20of%20the%20laser.%20The%20pictures%20show%20clearly%20the%20bolt%20followed%20the%20laser%20before%20touching%20the%20ground.%20%3Cp%3EHouard%2C%20A.%2C%20Walch%2C%20P.%2C%20Produit%2C%20T.%20et%20al.%20Nat.%20Photon%20(2023).%20https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs41566-022-01139-z.%20CC-BY%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ELightning-protection%20gear%20needs%20an%20upgrade%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20finding%20provides%20hope%20that%20lasers%20could%20one%20day%20offer%20a%20much-needed%20new%20avenue%20for%20protection%20against%20lightning%20bolts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELightning%20rods%2C%20which%20were%20invented%20by%20Benjamin%20Franklin%2C%20remain%20the%20best%20form%20of%20protection%20we've%20got%20against%20lightning%2C%20per%20a%20press%20release%20accompanying%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20their%20protection%20extends%20only%20as%20far%20as%20the%20rod%20is%20tall.%20That%20means%20a%2010-foot%20tall%20rod%20will%20protect%20anyone%20within%2010%20feet%20of%20the%20pole%2C%20but%20not%20any%20further%20than%20that%2C%20per%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20laser%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20could%20reach%20high%20in%20the%20clouds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20that%20the%20discharge%20could%20follow%20the%20beam%20for%20nearly%2060%20meters%20(196%20feet)%20before%20reaching%20the%20tower%2C%26quot%3B%20Wolf%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F01%2F20%2Fworld%2Flaser-lightning-rod-scn%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20that%20the%20laser%20%26quot%3Bincreased%20the%20radius%20of%20the%20protection%20surface%20from%20120%20meters%20(393%20feet)%20to%20180%20meters%20(590%20feet).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20step%20is%20to%20try%20to%20develop%20a%20laser%20that%20can%20reach%20even%20higher%20up%20in%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20possible%20in%20theory.%20Houart%20cautioned%2C%20however%2C%20that%20this%20technology%2