0year%20observed%20in%20September%20%E2%80%93%20following%20a%20record%20summer%20%E2%80%93%20have%20broken%20records%20by%20an%20extraordinary%20amount%2C%E2%80%9D%20Burgess%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20described%20the%20month%20as%20%E2%80%9Cextreme%E2%80%9D%2C%20crediting%20it%20for%20pushing%202023%20%E2%80%9Cinto%20the%20dubious%20honour%20of%20first%20place%20%E2%80%93%20on%20track%20to%20be%20the%20warmest%20year%20and%20around%201.4%20C%20above%20preindustrial%20average%20temperatures.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Wetter-than-average%E2%80%99%20September%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Europe%2C%20the%20month%20was%20not%20only%20the%20hottest%20on%20record%20but%20also%20one%20with%20%E2%80%9Cwetter-than-average%E2%80%9D%20conditions%20along%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20continent%E2%80%99s%20western%20seaboard%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fclimate-change-fueled-flooding-in-libya-greece-bulgaria-study%2Fa-66862911%5C%22%3Ecited%20the%20extreme%20rainfall%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20Greece%2C%20associated%20with%20Storm%20Daniel.%20The%20storm%20also%20caused%20devastating%20flooding%20in%20Libya%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Flibya-thousands-feared-dead-after-storm-daniel%2Fa-66783443%5C%22%3Ekilling%20thousands%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20largely%20destroying%20its%20eastern%20city%20of%20Derna.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20areas%20affected%20by%20rain%20in%20Europe%20include%C2%A0the%20western%20Iberian%20Peninsula%2C%20Ireland%2C%20northern%20Britain%2C%20and%20Scandinavia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBeyond%20Europe%2C%20the%20Latin%20American%20countries%20of%20Brazil%20and%20Chile%20also%20experienced%20what%20the%20report%20said%20were%20%E2%80%9Cextreme%20precipitation%20events%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%20the%20countries%E2%80%99%20southern%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20C3S%20is%20implemented%20by%20the%20European%20Center%20for%20Medium