%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Another%20Blow'%20to%20Press%20Freedom%20Under%20Modi%20Govt%2C%20Say%20Newspapers%20on%20'NewsClick'%20Raids%2C%20Arrests%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F12%2Fpress-freedom-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EEnglish%20newspapers%20across%20the%20country%20have%20unanimously%20condemned%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fterrorising-journalism-editorial%5C%22%3Eraids%20and%20arrests%20against%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20underlining%20that%20the%20latest%20episode%20marks%20a%20new%20low%20in%20terms%20of%20muzzling%20freedom%20of%20press%20under%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20described%20it%20as%20a%20case%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fundeclared-emergency-the-hindu-editorial-on-the-arrests-in-the-newsclick-case%2Farticle67380803.ece%5C%22%3Eundeclared%20emergency%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20editorial%20said%20slapping%20the%20draconian%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20against%20journalists%20amounted%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fdrawing-lines-in-cauvery-waters-8968776%2F%5C%22%3Ebrazen%20short-circuiting%20of%20the%20due%20process%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Canother%20blow%E2%80%9D%20for%20press%20freedom%20in%20India%20under%20the%20Modi%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20underlining%20that%20the%20government%20is%20yet%20to%20point%20to%20a%20specific%20allegation%20which%20merited%20the%20arrest%20and%20charging%20of%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20editor-in-chief%2C%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%2C%20and%20another%20employee%20of%20the%20media%20outlet%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20editorial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fundeclared-emergency-the-hindu-editorial-on-the-arrests-in-the-newsclick-case%2Farticle67380803.ece%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20for%20a%20government%20that%20has%20shown%20itself%20to%20be%20intolerant%20of%20critical%20journalism%2C%20the%20actions%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-led%20regime%20on%20the%20news%20website%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20smack%20of%20extreme%20vendetta%20and%20brazen%20harassment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20delves%20into%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20arrested%20persons%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20given%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%2C%20that%20Purkayastha%20has%20been%20granted%20protection%20by%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20from%20arrest%2C%20and%20that%20a%20lower%20court%20has%20also%20dismissed%20a%20complaint%20filed%20by%20the%20income%20tax%20department%20against%20the%20media%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%20claims%20that%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20proximate%20to%20the%20Chinese%20government%20and%20pushing%20its%20agenda%20against%20India%2C%20the%20editorial%20notes%20that%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20point%20to%20%E2%80%9Cany%20specific%20article%20on%20the%20site%20that%20amounted%20to%20illegal%20propaganda%20against%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGovernment%20representatives%20first%20engaged%20in%20a%20systematic%20vilification%20and%20disinformation%20campaign%20against%20the%20site%20based%20on%20this%20article.%20Tuesday%E2%80%99s%20actions%20seem%20driven%20by%20an%20impulse%20to%20scapegoat%20a%20media%20outlet%20and%20to%20bring%20about%2C%20therefore%2C%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20critical%20journalism.%20No%20government%20can%20or%20should%20so%20brazenly%20target%20journalists%20solely%20based%20on%20suspicion%20about%20its%20funding%20and%20thereby%20undermine%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20which%20is%20guaranteed%20under%20the%20Constitution%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fundeclared-emergency-the-hindu-editorial-on-the-arrests-in-the-newsclick-case%2Farticle67380803.ece%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20raids%20and%20arrests%20%E2%80%9Cunderlines%20apprehensions%20of%20Police-ED%20being%20weaponised%20and%20a%20draconian%20law%20being%20deployed%20to%20intimidate%20a%20media%20organisation%E2%80%9D.%20The%20arrests%20and%20raids%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E%20editorial%20says%2C%20raise%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20questions%20about%20press%20freedom%2C%20a%20crucial%20part%20of%20the%20citizens%E2%80%99%20fundamental%20right%20to%20know%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20noting%20that%20the%20state%20is%20fully%20within%20its%20rights%20to%20investigate%20the%20funding%20allegations%20against%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20editorial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fdrawing-lines-in-cauvery-waters-8968776%2F%5C%22%3Esays%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20state%20should%20not%20brazenly%20wrest%20more%20power%20to%20circumvent%20restraints%20under%20a%20stringent%20law%20that%2C%20in%20this%20matter%2C%20is%20clearly%20uncalled-for%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20the%20general%20principles%20of%20criminal%20law%20are%20reversed%2C%20timelines%20are%20relaxed%20for%20filing%20chargesheets%20and%20bail%20is%20immensely%20more%20difficult.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20recalled%20the%20observations%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20made%20in%20April%20this%20year%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-media-one-sealed-cover-analysis%5C%22%3EMediaOne%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Chief%20Justice%20had%20said%20%E2%8