IMG_1874-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20are%20accustomed%20to%20seeing%20social%20elites%20as%20powerful%20authorities%20like%20national%20leaders%2C%20business%20tycoons%2C%20cultural%20influencers%2C%20etc.%20However%2C%20any%20aberration%20in%20this%20norm%20becomes%20the%20talk%20of%20the%20town%20and%20invites%20scrutiny%20to%20understand%20the%20reasons%20behind%20such%20an%20occurrence.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20elevation%20of%20Draupadi%20Murmu%20as%20the%20President%20of%20India%20was%20not%20analysed%20as%20a%20normal%20event%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy.%20A%20curious%20investigation%20was%20initiated%20to%20examine%20her%20social%20location%2C%20gender%20conditionality%20and%20political%20trajectories%20in%20order%20to%20legitimise%20her%20appropriateness%20for%20the%20position.%20Similar%20curiosity%20and%20surprise%20was%20expressed%20by%20political%20pundits%20when%20K.%20R.%20Narayanan%20and%20Ramnath%20Kovind%20were%20elected%20as%20the%20presidents.%20Interestingly%2C%20when%20key%20positions%20of%20power%20are%20adorned%20by%20the%20social%20elites%2C%20no%20such%20shock%20or%20scrutiny%20is%20visible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20sense%20of%20comfort%20amongst%20certain%20Dalit-Bahujan%20groups%20that%20as%20a%20political%20class%2C%20they%20have%20a%20growing%20acceptability%20in%20democratic%20institutions%20as%20they%20also%20govern%20and%20influence%20certain%20regions%20and%20groups.%20However%2C%20this%20is%20a%20narrow%20understanding%20of%20power.%20The%20modern%20structures%20of%20power%20are%20diverse%2C%20multi-layered%20and%20create%20new%20spaces%20and%20institutions%20of%20influence.%20For%20example%2C%20interactions%20on%20social%20media%20appear%20free%2C%20participatory%20and%20non-discriminatory.%20However%2C%20in%20reality%20the%20social%20network%20can%20be%20utilised%20to%20serve%20the%20interest%20of%20certain%20corporate%20bodies%20or%20influential%20individuals.%20%E2%80%98Power%E2%80%99%20thus%20operates%20in%20non-political%20zones%20through%20some%20invisible%20hands%20that%20often%20serves%20traditional%20power%20authorities%20and%20retains%20their%20control%20over%20social%20and%20economic%20assets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20appears%20that%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20mass%20hardly%20investigates%20the%20processes%20and%20structures%20of%20power.%20It%20is%20overtly%20visible%20that%20the%20social%20elites%20dominate%20and%20exploit%20various%20sources%20and%20institutions%20of%20power%20and%20serve%20their%20particularistic%20class%20and%20social%20interests%2C%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20mass%20has%20not%20been%20very%20agitated%20by%20such%20a%20status%20quo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fthe-role-of-intellectuals-in-the-anti-caste-movement-lessons-from-ambedkars-academic-credentials%5C%22%3EThe%20Role%20of%20Intellectuals%20in%20the%20Anti-Caste%20Movement%3A%20Lessons%20from%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20Academic%20Credentials%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20there%20is%20revolutionary%20social%20thought%20and%20political%20consciousness%20available%20in%20the%20history%20of%20anti-caste%20and%20non-Brahmanical%20movements%20that%20has%20challenged%20the%20hegemonic%20domination%20of%20the%20social%20elites%20in%20the%20past%2C%20there%20are%20few%20flag%20bearers%2C%20intellectuals%20and%20social%20movements%20in%20the%20contemporary%20times%20that%20can%20claim%20to%20inherit%20the%20radical%20legacy.%20The%20exploitative%20domination%20of%20the%20social%20elites%20will%20not%20end%20until%20an%20enlightened%20Dalit-Bahujan%20mass%20decides%20to%20challenge%20the%20conventional%20authorities%20by%20embarking%20a%20mass%20movement%20for%20social%20justice%20and%20claim%20authoritative%20power%20into%20their%20own%20hands.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20social%20elite%20hegemony%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20modern%20economic%20and%20political%20arrangement%2C%20it%20is%20expected%20that%20the%20positions%20of%20power%20in%20any%20sector%20or%20discipline%20shall%20be%20open%20to%20all%20for%20fair%20competition.%20The%20liberal%20constitutional%20principles%20also%20suggest%20that%20any%20collective%20workforce%20shall%20represent%20the%20general%20plurality%20of%20the%20population%2C%20thus%20strengthening%20the%20democratic%20credentials%20of%20the%20society%20and%20economy.%20For%20a%20greater%20participation%20of%20diverse%20social%20groups%2C%20it%20is%20required%20that%20the%20new%20institutions%20shall%20provide%20effective%20assistance%20and%20safeguards%20to%20the%20disadvantaged%20groups%20and%20make%20them%20part%20of%20the%20mainstream%20economy.%20However%2C%20such%20moral%20principles%20are%20halfheartedly%20applied.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20modern%20institutions%20are%20undemocratic%2C%20and%20marked%20by%20the%20absence%20of%20poor%20and%20marginalised%20social%20groups%20in%20power%20structures%20while%20unapologetically%20functioning%20on%20the%20behalf%20of%20the%20dominant%20class%20elites.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20global%20phenomenon%20that%20the%20positions%20of%20power%20and%20authority%20are%20meant%20to%20be%20adorned%20by%20the%20social%20elites%20and%20rich%20classes%20(like%20the%20whites%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Europe)%20whereas%20the%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99%20groups%20(African%20Americans%2C%20Mexicans%20and%20other%20migrant%20communities)%20are%20expected%20to%20perform%20as%20the%20subordinates%2C%20as%20the%20peripheral%20workforce%20that%20perpetually%20remains%20dependent%20upon%20the%20mercies%20of%20the%20ruling%20classes.%20In%20India%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20the%20history%20of%20domination%20by%20the%20social%20elites%20is%20much%20older%20and%20perpetuated%20even%20in%20the%20current%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fambedkar-three-types-dictatorship%5C%22%3EAmbedkar%E2%80%99s%20Warnings%20About%20Three%20Types%20of%20Dictatorships%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAny%20cursory%20history%20of%20powerful%20positions%20in%20the%20central%20cabinet%2C%20higher%20judiciary%2C%20the%20chief%20authorities%20of%20the%20security%20forces%2C%20the%20editors%20of%20media%20house%2C%20CEOs%20of%20multinational%20corporations%2C%20the%20leading%20influencers%20in%20the%20cultural%20and%20sports%20industry%2C%20etc.%20will%20showcase%20that%20the%20social%20elites%20have%20been%20dominating%20these%20positions%20since%20the%20day%20of%20its%20origin.%20The%20Dalit-Bahujan%20%E2%80%98others%E2%80%99%20are%20the%20bewitched%20spectators%20of%20this%20phenomenon.%20They%20often%20operate%20as%20the%20passive%20and%20poor%20recipients%20of%20orders%20and%20profits%20showered%20over%20them%20by%20the%20philanthropist%20ruling%20elites.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIronically%2C%20there%20is%20no%20big%20conflict%20between%20the%20%E2%80%98haves%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98have%20nots%E2%80%99%20that%20may%20have%20resulted%20in%20challenging%20such%20exploitative%20social%20and%20class%20conditions.%20The%20lower%20social%20strata%20operate%20under%20the%20cultural%20hegemony%20of%20the%20social%20elites%20and%20find%20no%20hesitation%20in%20adoring%20them%20as%20the%20true%20heir%20of%20power%20and%20status.%20Large%20Dalit-Bahujan%20sections%20readily%20function%20as%20the%20comprador%20class%20of%20the%20traditional%20ruling%20classes%2C%20under%20the%20pretext%20that%20they%20are%20serving%20the%20national%20interest%20or%20protecting%20the%20Hindu%20religious%20values.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20they%20often%20look%20down%20on%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20majority%20lower%20caste%20communities%20as%20narrow%2C%20caste-based%2C%20political%20assertion%20and%20even%20anti-national%20at%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20inferiority%20complex%20amongst%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20masses%20provides%20legitimacy%20to%20the%20leadership%20and%20authority%20to%20the%20social%20elites.%20Though%20in%20modern%20social%20history%2C%20iconic%20leaders%20like%20Periyar%20Ramaswamy%20and%20Babasaheb%20Ambedkar%20destabilised%20such%20conventional%20norms%20and%20invited%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20mass%20to%20imagine%20themselves%20as%20the%20legitimate%20inheritors%20of%20power%20and%20prestige%2C%20their%20thoughts%20are%20undervalued%20in%20the%20current%20context.%20Instead%2C%20the%20social%20justice%20movement%20today%20is%20weak%2C%20peripheral%20and%20incapable%20of%20challenging%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20social%20elites.%20Further%2C%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20middle%20class%2C%20intellectuals%20and%20social%20activists%20also%20hesitate%20to%20claim%20the%20seat%20of%20power%20and%20provide%20a%20radical%20vision%20that%20can%20awaken%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20movement%20today%20from%20such%20slumber.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWitnessing%20the%20domination%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SCs)%20and%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(STs)%20comprise%20almost%2025%25%20of%20the%20national%20population.%20The%20state%20is%20mandated%20to%20provide%20reservations%20to%20the%20socially%20marginalised%20communities%20in%20the%20public%20sector%20jobs.%20The%20reservation%20policy%20opens%20a%20window%20to%20democratise%20the%20workforce%2C%20ensuring%20participation%20of%20the%20socially%20disadvantaged%20groups%20like%20the%20SCs%20and%20STs%20in%20the%20state%20institutions.%20However%2C%20the%20reservation%20policy%20ensures%20only%20a%20token%20presence%20of%20the%20rich%20social%20diversity%20of%20the%20majority%20population.%20Any%20inquiry%20about%20the%20social%20demography%20of%20state%20institutions%20will%20prove%20that%20the%20presence%20of%20SC%2FST%20and%20Other%20Backward%20Castes%20(OBCs)%20is%20marginal%2C%20or%20restricted%20to%20the%20lower%20strata%20of%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlmost%20no%20public%20institutions%20showed%20commitment%20in%20ensuring%20equitable%20and%20substantive%20representation%20of%20the%20marginalised%20social%20groups%20and%20following%20the%20directives%20of%20social%20justice%20policies%20effectively.%20For%20example%2C%20of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20faculty%20positions%20in%20the%2045%20central%20universities%2C%20the%20combined%20strength%20of%20SC%2FST%20and%20OBC%20faculties%20is%20not%20even%2015%25.%20It%20means%20that%20more%20than%2080%25of%20the%20positions%20are%20occupied%20by%20the%20social%20elites.%20Out%20of%2045%20vice%20chancellors%2C%20only%204%20belonged%20to%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20social%20strata%20and%20the%20same%20can%20be%20stated%20for%20other%20bodies%20in%20the%20institutions.%20The%20participation%20of%20the%20marginalised%20social%20groups%20in%20other%20elite%20institutions%20like%20the%20IITs%20and%20IIMs%20is%20even%20lesser.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fiit-iim-reservation-appointment-merit-inclusivity%5C%22%3EHow%20Meritorious%20and%20Inclusive%20Are%20Our%20Institutions%20of%20Higher%20Education%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20key%20positions%20of%20power%20in%20most%20of%20the%20public%20institutions%20remain%20under%20the%20exclusive%20clutch%20of%20the%20social%20elites.%20Even%20after%20the%20announcement%20of%20reservation%20policy%20for%20the%20OBCs%20in%202006%2C%20the%20otherwise%20dominant%20middle%20castes%20(like%20the%20Yadavs)%2C%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20challenge%20the%20conventional%20control%20of%20social%20elites%20over%20state%20institutions.%20Further%2C%20outside%20the%20state%20institutions%2C%20their%20participation%20in%20the%20private%20economy%20as%20the%20bearers%20of%20capitalist%20economic%20assets%20is%20also%20miniscule.%20The%20top%20business%20houses%2C%20capitalist%20enterprises%2C%20cultural%20institutions%20and%20corporate%20bodies%20are%20dominated%20by%20the%20exclusive%20clubs%20of%20social%20elites%20and%20the%20rest%20operate%20as%20the%20low-key%20functionaries.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20future%20of%20the%20social%20justice%20movement%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20undemocratic%20and%20immoral%20that%20the%20positions%20of%20power%2C%20authority%20and%20high%20status%20are%20overtly%20dominated%20by%20the%20social%20elite%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejunta%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20majority%20of%20the%20population%20is%20thus%20forced%20to%20perform%20under%20the%20dictates%20of%20an%20exclusive%20club%20of%20social%20elites.%20With%20effective%20social%20networks%20and%20historic%20privileges%2C%20a%20small%20minority%20holds%20the%20most%20powerful%20positions.%20It%20helps%20them%20to%20serve%20their%20own%20class%20interests%20and%20cultural%20objectives%20effectively%20while%20neglecting%20the%20demands%20and%20problems%20associated%20with%20the%20Dalit-Bahujan%20groups.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20a%20scenario%20is%20disheartening%20as%20the%20national%20government%20often%20makes%20promises%20to%20ensure%20equitable%20participation%20of%20these%20groups%20in%20the%20mainstream%20work%20force%20but%20consistently%20fails%20to%20substantively%20implement%20the%20reservation%20policy%20at%20any%20level.%20Ironically%2C%20there%20is%20also%20a%20visible%20absence%20of%20strong%20political%20and%20social%20movement%20demanding%20equitable%20participation%20of%20the%20marginalised%20social%20groups%20in%20these%20positions%20of%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20general%20mobilisation%20of%20Dalit-Bahujan%20groups%20occur%20mainly%20during%20the%20legislative%20elections%2C%20to%20protest%20against%20caste%20atrocities%20or%20during%20certain%20social%20and%20cultural%20events.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20few%20public%20mobilisations%20or%20sustained%20protest%20demonstrations%20to%20demand%20swift%20and%20effective%20implementation%20of%20the%20reservation%20policy%20in%20all%20public%20sectors.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20public%20uproar%20or%20challenge%20against%20the%20current%20status%20quo%2C%20the%20government%20is%20comfortable%20in%20retaining%20and%20protecting%20the%20domination%20of%20social%20elites%20over%20state%20institutions.%20Since%20Dalit-Bahujan%20groups%20are%20mostly%20uninfluential%2C%20peripheral%20and%20passive%2C%20the%20structure%20of%20power%20has%20become%20an%20oligarchic%20and%20exclusive%20domain%20of%20the%20social%20elites%E2%80%99%20hegemony.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fharish-s-wankhede%5C%22%3EHarish%20S.%20Wankhede%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20Assistant%20Professor%2C%20Center%20for%20Political%20Studies%2C%20School%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%2C%20New%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696473015000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F14124741%2FIMG_1874-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fthe-missing-question-of-power-in-the-dalit-bahujan-discourse%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20are%20few%20flag%20bearers%2C%20intellectuals%20and%20social%20movements%20in%20the%20contemporary%20times%20that%20can%20claim%20to%20inherit%20the%20radical%20legacy%20of%20anti-caste%20movements%20of%20the%20past.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fthe-missing-question-of-power-in-the-dalit-bahujan-discourse%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hungary's%20foreign%20minister%20hints%20that%20Budapest%20will%20continue%20blocking%20EU%20military%20aid%2