mpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mohammed%20Faizal%20Disqualified%20as%20Lakshadweep%20MP%20a%20Day%20After%20Kerala%20HC%20Refused%20To%20Stay%20Conviction%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F14133347%2FUntitled-design-13.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Mohammed%20Faizal%20was%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20October%204%2C%20disqualified%20as%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20member%20from%20Lakshadweep%20following%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20on%20Tuesday%20to%20suspend%20his%20conviction%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20murder%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20view%20of%20order%20dated%2003.10.2023%20of%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20High%20Court%20of%20Kerala%2C%20Shri%20Mohammed%20Faizal%20P.P.%2C%20Member%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20representing%20the%20Lakshadweep%20Parliamentary%20Constituency%20of%20the%20Union%20Territory%20of%20Lakshadweep%2C%20stands%20disqualified%20from%20the%20membership%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20from%20the%20date%20of%20his%20conviction%2C%20i.e.%2011th%20January%2C%202023%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20Lok%20Sabha%20Secretariat%20bulletin%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20time%20that%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP)%20leader%20has%20been%20disqualified.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20high%20court%20refused%20to%20suspend%20his%20conviction%20but%20suspended%20the%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fhigh-court%2Fkerala-high-court%2Fkerala-high-court-mp-mohammed-faizal-conviction-disqualification-of-mp-mla-criminal-antecedents-239226%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Justice%20N.%20Nagaresh%20said%20that%20criminalisation%20of%20the%20election%20process%20is%20of%20grave%20concern%20to%20democracy%20and%20if%20persons%20with%20criminal%20antecedents%20are%20permitted%20to%20continue%20as%20elected%20representatives%20even%20after%20conviction%20by%20a%20competent%20court%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20would%20only%20send%20wrong%20signals%20to%20public%20at%20large%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%3EThe%20judge%20said%20that%20a%20conviction%20can%20only%20be%20suspended%20under%20section%20389%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC)%20if%20the%20Court%20was%20satisfied%20that%20the%20case%20was%20frivolous.%20He%20said%20conviction%20can%20be%20suspended%20if%20the%20court%20is%20satisfied%20that%20the%20convicted%20person%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20suffer%20from%20a%20certain%20disqualification%20or%20damage%20that%20cannot%20be%20undone%E2%80%9D%20only%20in%20rare%20cases%2C%20under%20special%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-reader-unique-id%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%3EThe%20high%20court%20relied%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20recent%20decision%20to%20suspend%20the%20conviction%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20which%20said%20that%20conviction%20%E2%80%9Ccannot%20be%20suspended%20by%20only%20looking%20at%20the%20ramifications%E2%80%9D%20but%20after%20considering%20all%20relevant%20aspects.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20Faizal%20and%20three%20others%20were%20convicted%20for%20attempting%20to%20murder%20a%20Congress%20leader%E2%80%99s%20son-in-law%20during%20the%202009%20general%20elections.%20The%20court%20sentenced%20him%20to%2010%20years%20in%20jail%2C%20which%20led%20to%20his%20automatic%20disqualification%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20A%20couple%20of%20weeks%20later%2C%20another%20single-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%20suspended%20his%20conviction.%20The%20thrust%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20was%20on%20the%20expenditure%20to%20the%20exchequer%20that%20the%20by-election%20would%20cause.%20He%20was%20eventually%20reinstated%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-mohammed-faizal-mp-suspension-set-aside%5C%22%3Eset%20aside%20that%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20asking%20the%20high%20court%20to%20consider%20the%20matter%20afresh.%20It%20said%20that%20if%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20was%20allowed%20to%20stand%2C%20the%20conviction%20and%20sentence%20of%20every%20elected%20politician%20would%20have%20to%20be%20suspended%20to%20avoid%20the%20financial%20burden%20of%20bye-elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20at%206%3A44%20pm%20on%20October%203%2C%202023%20and%20republished%20at%2010%3A05%20pm%20on%20October%204%2C%202023%20after%20Faizal%20was%20disqualified%20as%20an%20MP.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696437313000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F14133347%2FUntitled-design-13.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkerala-hc-refuses-stay-conviction-lakshadweep-mp-mohammed-faizal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20said%20that%20criminalisation%20of%20election%20process%20is%20of%20grave%20concern%20to%20democracy%20and%20if%20persons%20with%20criminal%20antecedents%20are%20permitted%20to%20continue%20as%20elected%20representatives%2C%20that%20would%20only%20send%20wrong%20signals%20to%20public%20at%20large.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkerala-hc-refuses-stay-conviction-lakshadweep-mp-mohammed-faizal%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Dozens%20of%20cats'%20found%20abandoned%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20desert%20as%20authorities%20launch%20investigation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696437180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-cat-abu-dhabi_6309014.jpg%3F20231004173908%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fabu-dhabi-dozens-of-cats-found-abandoned-in-de